!begin_node vqt_devinfo

(!begin_liste) [Availability]

!item [Name:]
ØInquire device status infoÆ - Inquire status of the output device.

!item [Opcode:]
248

!item [Syntax:]
void vqt_devinfo ( int16_t handle, int16_t device, int16_t *devexits, int8_t *devname );

!item [Description:]
The call vqt_devinfo checks whether a driver for a given output device has been
installed. The following apply:

!begin_xlist !short [device_name]
!item [Parameter]
Meaning
!item [~]
~
!item [handle]
Workstation identifier
!item [device]
Device ID (0..99)
!item [devexits]
!begin_xlist !short
!item [-1 =]
Error
!item [~0 =]
Device not installed
!item [~1 =]
Device installed
!end_xlist

!item [devname]
Device name
!end_xlist

!item [(!nolink [Return]) value:]
The function does not return a result.

!item [Availability:]
Only with FONTGDOS, FSM or SpeedoGDOS.

!item [Group:]
Inquire functions

!item [See also:]
(!link [Binding] [Bindings for vqt_devinfo]) ~ vq_devinfo ~ vq_ext_devinfo ~
(!link [GDOS][About the GDOS]) ~ SpeedoGDOS ~ NVDI

(!ende_liste)
!end_node



